column12: Epitope
Epitope Comments
The epitope was synthesized with two additional N-terminal residues (CK).

C1 residue doesn’t belong to the natural sequence, it was added to aid in coupling of carrier protein. Protein name stands for rhoptry protein 10. It was identified by TOF-MS of purified rhoptries' proteins, and peptide was synthesized and used for immunization of mice. The immune sera immunofluoresce pattern allowed for source protein identification as a rhoptry protein.
A panel of 84 nonamers were generated in order to identify epitopes within the surface antigen 1 (SAG1) of T. gondii.
The epitope was an exact to a sequence from the Homo sapiens host species.
Source protein also known as Surface antigen 1.

Truncation analysis reveals this region is epitopic in some toxoplasmosis patients in either serum alone or both in serum and ocular fluid. No sequence information in manuscript, sequence derived from Swiss Prot, assuming aa numbering is the same as in paper.

The authors indicate that the epitope sequence they provided are amino acids 296-345 of GRA4. But in fact, this sequence matches with amino acids 297-345 in the existent SwissProt record of GRA4 (the source protein).

Truncation analysis reveals this region is epitopic in some toxoplasmosis patients in either serum alone or both in serum and ocular fluid. No sequence information in manuscript, sequence derived from Swiss Prot, assuming aa numbering is the same as in paper.

Predicted B cell epitope, it was used to obtain rabbit polyclonal antibodies, shown to recognize source protein in WB and in intracellular parasites. Novel protein from source species. Shown to be a soluble constituent of tachyzoites, and suggested to be called ROP9.

The algorithm of the HLA-A2 peptide binding motif was predicted to have a leucine in position  2 and a valine in position 9 as anchors.  Peptide SAG1 212-220 was therefore generated to test antigenicity and MHC binding.
